The Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi , has elucidated that Osun faithful are not idol worshippers.<img src="https://i0.wp.com/instablog9ja.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/instablog9ja_20200726_17.jpg?resize=1024%2C1024" />The monarch who spoke on Saturday, in his palace when he received devotees as the ancient city celebrated the Osun festival, said that the festival is the celebration of water , noting that water is life . “We’re using this instance to reconnect with our Creator through nature to cleanse the world, and especially to end the pandemic. We are remembering our ancestors and it is unfair to call us idol worshipers,” he said. He also revealed that the festival was restricted as they had to abide by the NCDC guidelines in a bid to reduce the spread of corona virus. Original Article Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world. Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi, Ojaja II The Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Ogunwusi, Ojaja II, has described the late Afenifere leader, Pa Ayo Fasanmi, as a man of accomplishments, who brought dignity to all descendants of Oduduwa. The was contained in a tribute signed by his Director… August 1, 2020 In "News" Ooni Ogunwusi amidst traditional rulers and the people of Ife during Olojo festival. THE annual Olojo festival celebrated amidst funfare and glamour reached the climax, on Saturday, in Ile-Ife, as the Ooni of Ife, Oba Adeyeye Enitan Ogunwusi emerged from the Emese court within the Ile Oodua, donning the historical… October 1, 2017 In "News" Ile-ife—THE Ooni of  Ife, Oba Enitan Babatunde Adeyeye Ogunwusi, has expressed confidence in the ability of the new Aare Onakakanfo of Yorubaland, Aare Gani Adams, to unite the Yorubaland. *His Imperial Majesty, Ooni Enitan Adeyeye Ogunwusi, Ojaja II, the Ooni of Ife (centre), Miss Oluwatosin Shola-Shittu, the new Queen Moremi… January 24, 2018 In "News"